1..Search file name using Pattern in any file/directory
grep <pattern> <filename or any path or leave if searching in same folder>

2..Invert Match for non-matching lines  -v
grep -v <pattern> 

3..Silent search using -q and to get result , use echo $? for result

grep -q <pattern>

Here no output will be shown , wheather found or not found

Later, run echo $?
  if result if found,above command will display 1
  else display 0

4..
